<subSubSection id="77A250A2FECE870AD99DC33EFEDC7C45" pageId="280" pageNumber="281" type="description">
<paragraph id="3F070329FECE870AD99DC33EFEDC7C45" blockId="280.[136,778,278,368]" pageId="280" pageNumber="281">
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFECE870AD99DC33EFEE47C1E" authorityName="Gunther" authorityYear="1887" box="[136,259,278,299]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Trachonurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="280" pageNumber="281" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFECE870AD99DC33EFEE47C1E" box="[136,259,278,299]" italics="true" pageId="280" pageNumber="281">Trachonurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
G̹nther, 1887:124 (subgenus of 
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFECE870ADB78C33FFD2B7C19" box="[621,716,279,300]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Macrurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="280" pageNumber="281" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFECE870ADB78C33FFD2B7C19" box="[621,716,279,300]" italics="true" pageId="280" pageNumber="281">Macrurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<typeStatus id="E003BD8BFECE870ADBF5C33FFCEE7C19" box="[736,777,279,300]" pageId="280" pageNumber="281">type</typeStatus>
species: 
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFECE870AD804C310FE187C78" authorityName="Gunther" authorityYear="1877" box="[273,511,312,333]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Coryphaenoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="280" pageNumber="281" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="villosus">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFECE870AD804C310FE187C78" box="[273,511,312,333]" italics="true" pageId="280" pageNumber="281">Coryphaenoides villosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
G̹nther, 1887, by original designation).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="77A250A2FECE870AD99DC3B3FF0479D3" pageId="280" pageNumber="281" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="3F070329FECE870AD99DC3B3FF0479D3" blockId="280.[136,778,411,1968]" pageId="280" pageNumber="281">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFECE870AD99DC3B3FEE57C80" bold="true" box="[136,258,411,437]" pageId="280" pageNumber="281">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Anus surrounded by broad, extensive periproct that extending most of distance between anal-fin origin and pelvic-fin bases; periproct abutting anal-fin origin. Infraorbital ridge not connected with preopercular ridge, separated by distinct gap. Pelvic fin with 6–7 soft rays, its origin distinctly posterior to vertical through pectoral-fin base (usually below midbase of first dorsal fin). Second spinous ray of first dorsal fin slender, lacking serrations along its leading edge.Chin barbel present.Teeth in narrow band in upper jaw, with outer series usually enlarged; lower jaw teeth in 2–3 rows or narrow band. Scales not deciduous, closely adhered to body surfaces. Body scales adherent, covered with long, erect, needle-like spinules in quincunx pattern; buttresses well developed; reticulate pattern developed over entire scale surface. Scales along anterior parts of second dorsal and anal fins enlarged. Grooved lateral line present or absent. Head almost fully scaled; gular and branchiostegal membranes heavily scaled in most species; no scutes on head ridges and tip and lateral angles of snout. Cephalic sensory canals lacking open pores. Pyloric caeca short and thick, usually less than 15. Branchiostegal rays 7. Body uniformly dark, lacking prominent silvery reflection. [Modified from 
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FECE870AD99DC681FE3179F6" author="Sazonov, Y. I. &amp; Iwamoto, T." box="[136,470,1193,1220]" pageId="280" pageNumber="281" pagination="27 - 95" refId="ref298977" refString="Sazonov, Y. I. &amp; Iwamoto, T. (1992) Grenadiers (Pisces, Gadiformes) of the Nazca and Sala y Gomez Ridges, southeastern Pacific. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 48, 27 - 95." type="journal article" year="1992">Sazonov &amp; Iwamoto (1992)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FECE870ADB0FC682FF3E79D3" author="Iwamoto, T. &amp; Graham, K. J." pageId="280" pageNumber="281" pagination="407 - 509" refId="ref288409" refString="Iwamoto, T. &amp; Graham, K. J. (2001) Grenadiers (families Bathygadidae and Macrouridae, Gadiformes, Pisces) of New South Wales, Australia. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 52, 407 - 509." type="journal article" year="2001">Iwamoto &amp; Graham (2001)</bibRefCitation>
.]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="77A250A2FECE870AD9A8C6C5FDD27A85" pageId="280" pageNumber="281" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="3F070329FECE870AD9A8C6C5FDD27A85" blockId="280.[136,778,411,1968]" pageId="280" pageNumber="281">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFECE870AD9A8C6C5FED67832" bold="true" box="[189,305,1261,1287]" pageId="280" pageNumber="281">Remarks.</emphasis>
Although 
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFECE870AD8ACC6C5FDAF7832" authorityName="Gunther" authorityYear="1887" box="[441,584,1261,1287]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Trachonurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="280" pageNumber="281" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFECE870AD8ACC6C5FDAF7832" box="[441,584,1261,1287]" italics="true" pageId="280" pageNumber="281">Trachonurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a distinctive genus of the family, there is much discussion on its species-level classification. It is still uncertain how many species are included in this group, and there appears to be some species still remaining to be described (
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FECE870ADBBDC75DFEA97884" author="Sazonov, Y. I. &amp; Iwamoto, T." pageId="280" pageNumber="281" pagination="27 - 95" refId="ref298977" refString="Sazonov, Y. I. &amp; Iwamoto, T. (1992) Grenadiers (Pisces, Gadiformes) of the Nazca and Sala y Gomez Ridges, southeastern Pacific. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 48, 27 - 95." type="journal article" year="1992">Sazonov &amp; Iwamoto 1992</bibRefCitation>
; Iwamoto 1997; 
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FECE870ADB1AC7B0FF2478E1" author="Iwamoto, T. &amp; McMillan, P." pageId="280" pageNumber="281" pagination="255 - 259" refId="ref288623" refString="Iwamoto, T. &amp; McMillan, P. (1997) A new grenadier, genus Trachonurus, from New Zealand and Australia (Pisces: Gadiformes: Macrouridae). Memoirs of the Museum of Victoria, 56, 255 - 259." type="journal article" year="1997">Iwamoto &amp; McMillan 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FECE870AD9C1C792FDE578E1" author="Iwamoto, T. &amp; Merrett, N. R." box="[212,514,1466,1492]" pageId="280" pageNumber="281" pagination="473 - 570" refId="ref288733" refString="Iwamoto, T. &amp; Merrett, N. R. (1997) Pisces Gadiformes: taxonomy of grenadiers of the New Caledonian region, southwest Pacific. Memoires du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, 176, 473 - 570." type="journal article" year="1997">Iwamoto &amp; Merrett 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FECE870ADB06C792FF2378C3" author="Iwamoto, T. &amp; Williams, A." pageId="280" pageNumber="281" pagination="105 - 243" refId="ref289322" refString="Iwamoto, T. &amp; Williams, A. (1999) Grenadiers (Pisces, Gadiformes) from the continental slope of western and northwestern Australia. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 51, 105 - 243." type="journal article" year="1999">Iwamoto &amp; Williams 1999</bibRefCitation>
). The following six species are currently regarded as valid, one of which is known from Japanese waters: 
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFECE870AD99DC408FD867B0F" authority="Iwamoto &amp; McMillan, 1997" authorityName="Iwamoto &amp; McMillan" authorityYear="1997" box="[136,609,1567,1594]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Trachonurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="280" pageNumber="281" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gagates">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFECE870AD99DC408FEE67B0C" box="[136,257,1568,1593]" italics="true" pageId="280" pageNumber="281">T. gagates</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FECE870AD81AC408FD867B0F" author="Iwamoto, T. &amp; McMillan, P." box="[271,609,1567,1594]" pageId="280" pageNumber="281" pagination="255 - 259" refId="ref288623" refString="Iwamoto, T. &amp; McMillan, P. (1997) A new grenadier, genus Trachonurus, from New Zealand and Australia (Pisces: Gadiformes: Macrouridae). Memoirs of the Museum of Victoria, 56, 255 - 259." type="journal article" year="1997">Iwamoto &amp; McMillan, 1997</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
distributed in 
<collectingCountry id="47AF43B9FECE870AD99DC469FF087B6E" box="[136,239,1601,1627]" name="Australia" pageId="280" pageNumber="281">Australia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="47AF43B9FECE870AD825C46AFE287B6E" box="[304,463,1601,1628]" name="New Zealand" pageId="280" pageNumber="281">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
; 
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFECE870AD8CAC46AFCED7B69" authority="Iwamoto, 1997" authorityName="Iwamoto" authorityYear="1997" box="[479,778,1601,1628]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Trachonurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="280" pageNumber="281" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="robinsi">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFECE870AD8CAC46AFDA97B6E" box="[479,590,1601,1627]" italics="true" pageId="280" pageNumber="281">T. robinsi</emphasis>
Iwamoto, 1997
</taxonomicName>
probably endemic to the 
<collectingCountry id="47AF43B9FECE870AD889C44BFDF97B48" box="[412,542,1635,1661]" name="Philippines" pageId="280" pageNumber="281">Philippines</collectingCountry>
; 
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFECE870ADB3DC44CFEAD7B95" authority="Gilbert &amp; Cramer, 1897" authorityName="Gilbert &amp; Cramer" authorityYear="1897" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Trachonurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="280" pageNumber="281" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sentipellis">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFECE870ADB3DC44CFD527B48" box="[552,693,1635,1661]" italics="true" pageId="280" pageNumber="281">T. sentipellis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FECE870ADBAFC44BFEAD7B95" author="Gilbert, C. H. &amp; Cramer, F." pageId="280" pageNumber="281" pagination="403 - 435" refId="ref285862" refString="Gilbert, C. H. &amp; Cramer, F. (1897) Report on the fishes dredged in deep water near the Hawaiian Islands, with descriptions and figures of twenty-three new species. Proceedings of the United States National Museum 19, 403 - 435, pls. XXXVI-XLVIII. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.19 - 1114.403" type="journal article" year="1897">Gilbert &amp; Cramer, 1897</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
recorded from the Hawaiian Islands, 
<collectingCountry id="47AF43B9FECE870AD99DC48FFF157BF4" box="[136,242,1703,1729]" name="Australia" pageId="280" pageNumber="281">Australia</collectingCountry>
, the New Caledonian region, and 
<collectingCountry id="47AF43B9FECE870ADB9AC48FFD027BF4" box="[655,741,1703,1729]" name="Taiwan" pageId="280" pageNumber="281">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
; 
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFECE870ADBE0C480FDE37BD1" authority="(Goode &amp; Bean, 1885)" baseAuthorityName="Goode &amp; Bean" baseAuthorityYear="1885" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Trachonurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="280" pageNumber="281" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sulcatus">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFECE870ADBE0C480FF037BD6" italics="true" pageId="280" pageNumber="281">T. sulcatus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FECE870AD9EDC4E1FE1C7BD1" author="Goode, G. B. &amp; Bean, T. H." box="[248,507,1737,1764]" pageId="280" pageNumber="281" pagination="589 - 605" refId="ref286338" refString="Goode, G. B. &amp; Bean, T. H. (1885) Descriptions of new fishes obtainedbytheUnitedStatesFishCommissionmainlyfrom deep water off the Atlantic and Gulf coasts. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 8, 589 - 605. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.8 - 543.589" type="journal article" year="1885">Goode &amp; Bean, 1885</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, a senior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFECE870AD99DC4C4FE1F7A33" authority="(Vaillant, 1888)" baseAuthorityName="Vaillant" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[136,504,1771,1798]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Trachonurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="280" pageNumber="281" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="asperrimus">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFECE870AD99DC4C4FECC7A30" box="[136,299,1772,1797]" italics="true" pageId="280" pageNumber="281">T. asperrimus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FECE870AD851C4C3FE177A33" author="Vaillant, L. L." box="[324,496,1771,1798]" pageId="280" pageNumber="281" refId="ref302231" refString="Vaillant, L. L. (1888) Expeditions Scientifiques du &quot; Travailleur &quot; et du &quot; Talisman &quot; Pendant les Annees 1880, 1881, 1882, 1883. Poissons. G. Masson, Paris, 406 pp., 28 pls. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 98313" type="book" year="1888">Vaillant, 1888</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, widely distributed in the Atlantic; 
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFECE870AD836C526FE7D7A12" authorityName="Gunther" authorityYear="1877" box="[291,410,1805,1831]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Coryphaenoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="280" pageNumber="281" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="villosus">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFECE870AD836C526FE7D7A12" box="[291,410,1805,1831]" italics="true" pageId="280" pageNumber="281">T. villosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(G̹nther, 1877) (
<typeStatus id="E003BD8BFECE870ADB67C526FD437A1D" box="[626,676,1806,1832]" pageId="280" pageNumber="281">type</typeStatus>
species) probably confined to the northwestern Pacific from 
<collectingCountry id="47AF43B9FECE870ADBDFC518FCED7A7F" box="[714,778,1840,1866]" name="Japan" pageId="280" pageNumber="281">Japan</collectingCountry>
to the 
<collectingCountry id="47AF43B9FECE870AD9D9C579FEAD7A5E" box="[204,330,1873,1899]" name="Philippines" pageId="280" pageNumber="281">Philippines</collectingCountry>
(see the Remarks of this species); and 
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFECE870ADBE0C57AFDD37ABB" authority="Iwamoto &amp; Williams, 1999" authorityName="Iwamoto &amp; Williams" authorityYear="1999" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Trachonurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="280" pageNumber="281" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="yiwardaus">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFECE870ADBE0C57AFF1B7AB8" italics="true" pageId="280" pageNumber="281">T. yiwardaus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FECE870AD817C55CFDD37ABB" author="Iwamoto, T. &amp; Williams, A." box="[258,564,1907,1934]" pageId="280" pageNumber="281" pagination="105 - 243" refId="ref289322" refString="Iwamoto, T. &amp; Williams, A. (1999) Grenadiers (Pisces, Gadiformes) from the continental slope of western and northwestern Australia. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 51, 105 - 243." type="journal article" year="1999">Iwamoto &amp; Williams, 1999</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
so far known from the west and south coasts of 
<collectingCountry id="47AF43B9FECE870AD8D2C5BEFDD67A85" box="[455,561,1942,1968]" name="Australia" pageId="280" pageNumber="281">Australia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
